The paper discusses a new framework for scalable Cell-Free Massive MIMO systems, which involves algorithms for initial access, pilot assignment, cluster formation, precoding, and combining. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). However, given the focus on wireless networks and signal processing, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.AI.
